-- AES Agrees to Sell ‘Substantial Majority’ of Chinese Businesses
-- B y   T i n a   D a v i s
-- 2012-05-07T12:12:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/aes-agrees-to-sell-substantial-majority-of-chinese-businesses.html
AES Corp. (AES)  has signed two agreements to
sell “a substantial majority” of its Chinese businesses for
$134 million.  The agreements include selling stakes in a coal-fired power
plant and a windpower joint venture to Sembcorp Utilities and
the previously announced sale of a stake in a development
company to its joint venture partner, China Three Gorges New
Energy Corp., the company said in a statemtnt today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tina Davis at 
 tinadavis@bloomberg.net  